Gelasio Italic (Gelasio-Italic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Gelasio-Italic', Everything looks good.

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'Gelasio-Medium', Everything looks good.

Gelasio Medium Regular (Gelasio-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Gelasio' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Gelasio Medium'.

Pass

Gelasio Medium Regular (Gelasio-Medium.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Gelasio Medium Italic (Gelasio-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Gelasio-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Gelasio Medium Italic (Gelasio-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Gelasio' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Gelasio Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

NID 6 is 'Gelasio-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Gelasio SemiBold Regular (Gelasio-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Gelasio' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Gelasio SemiBold'.

Pass

Gelasio SemiBold Italic (Gelasio-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Gelasio' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Gelasio SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Gelasio Bold (Gelasio-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Gelasio-Bold', Everything looks good.
